<div class="lp"><section class="hero"><div class="hi">
<p class="kicker">Web / APIs</p>
<h1>Dynamic Website Content with High Relevance for Your Layout</h1>
<p>Dynamic website content supplements the design of your online shop with changing control elements such as advertising banners or opt-in boxes. We develop these elements with such connections that they do not change your layout, but supplement it in the short term with your campaign information. We work with the features of the innovative Shopware 6 shop system for this.</p>
</div></section>
<div class="content">
<h2>Dynamic Website Content, Developed by Hob by Horse for Your Business Model</h2>
<p>Dynamic website content adapts to the needs of target groups. At the same time, it must meet the technical requirements of search engines. There are always changes in the evaluation criteria regarding load time, visit duration or layout stability. Through individual developments for e-commerce, we keep your online shop constantly up to date with these updates. This technically improves your ranking in search engines and emotionally improves the shopping experience and communication with your visitors.</p>

<h2>Dynamic Website Content – Content Examples with SEO Evaluation Relevance</h2>
<p>The following criteria are a sample list of developments by Hob by Horse according to the current standards of the largest global search engines:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift):</strong> A stable page layout means that existing interactive control elements or scroll activities do not lead to a layout shift. With our development work, we achieve pixel values vertically and horizontally of less than 0.1.</li>
<li><strong>FID (First Input Delay):</strong> This measures the speed between clicking and page loading. A value of less than 100 milliseconds is rewarded by search engines with a good ranking and corresponds to the fleeting moment available to you for further interactions or leaving your online shop.</li>
<li><strong>LCP (Largest Contentful Paint):</strong> Most visitors lose complex online shops due to too long a loading time. What gets clicked is what feels like it loads immediately and remains stably usable. The main content is measured and for the ranking the loading time of the largest graphic, animated and descriptive element. We develop dynamic website content according to this criterion for a loading time of under, at most 2.5 seconds.</li>
</ul>
<p>Search engines refer to these criteria as "Web Vitals" — indicators of the vitality/user adaptation of an online shop. Any problems that may exist can be found and fixed with Shopware 6 individually for each business model.</p>

<h2>Dynamic Website Content for All Industries Worldwide</h2>
<p>A small online shop in retail with a regional setup loses most customers due to too slow a response to interactions. Searchers for food, fashion items or advice and services in the lifestyle sector have an abundance of options, of which only the fastest guarantee promising customer retention. For the ranking of your online shop and the optimal visibility among target groups, the individual development of dynamic website content is decisive for success.</p>

<h2>Target Groups for Layout Design with Dynamic Website Content by Hob by Horse</h2>
<p>In B2B trade, companies search for products and services from other commercial providers in their industry. Search engines must equally quickly be available to the B2C target group — end consumers. Manufacturers have better D2C positioning with well-integrated dynamic website content to offer their products to end consumers without intermediaries.</p>
<p>Is your dynamic website content too slow or disruptive to the layout of your online shop? Call Hob by Horse for individual developments or commission a new development for better shopping experiences by email!</p>
</div></div>
